
# self-company private memory — never commit (Chairman privacy)
.company/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Build scratch
.*-manifest*.md
.translation-glossary.md

# Local Claude config — entirely private, never committed. A skill repo's
# deliverable is its ROOT content (SKILL.md, scripts/, ...), not a committed
# .claude/. The dev-only symlinks under .claude/skills/self-company/ (which let
# THIS repo load itself as a skill) are regenerated locally via
# scripts/dev-link-skill.sh — committing symlinks is non-portable (Windows / git
# archive). Hooks (.claude/settings.json) are an opt-in LOCAL install via
# install-hook.sh; settings.local.json is the machine-specific permission file.
.claude/
